17:{"id":"food-inflation","categoryId":"inflation","title":"Food & Non-Alcoholic Beverages CPI","value":"2.9%","rawValue":2.9,"unit":"%","change":-0.7,"changeLabel":"from March 2026 (3.6%)","trend":"down","description":"Food and non-alcoholic beverage inflation eased to 2.9% in April 2026, continuing its decline from 2023 highs above 14%. Strong farm output has moderated food prices. Meat prices remain elevated year-on-year despite recent monthly declines. Bread and cereals saw mixed trends.","source":"$18","lastUpdated":"2026-05-21","series":"$19"}
